overall_success_pre_1: Intention/Goal Success    When you consider the intentions or goals that you have for yourself, to what degree do you feel like you are successful in actually accomplishing those goals?     Please consider both big and small intentions or goals.    	100% success rate would mean that you are able to accomplish ALL of your goals/intentions. 	50% success rate would mean that you are able to accomplish about HALF of your goals/intentions. - Goal success rate (%)
action_day_actual_1: End of Day | Actual     Please estimate to what extent, on AVERAGE, you achieve your goals, intentions, tasks and responsibilities on a DAILY basis.    For example, at the END OF THE DAY when you think about all of the things you hoped to do that day, what percentage do you usually accomplish? - % success
action_day_belief_1: Beginning of Day | Belief     A similar question but...     Now we would like to know at the BEGINNING OF EACH DAY, what percentage of your DAILY goals, tasks and responsibilities do you BELIEVE you will accomplish? In other words, sometimes we set goals for ourselves without really believing we’ll get to them, but at least hoping we will. We want you to estimate what percentage of your goals you really, honestly believe you will accomplish each day. - % success belief

ib_domains_goal_1: Domain Questions     Below we list a wide variety of categories where you may have goals.    We would like to know, for each category, whether or not you have actual goals for that particular category. Remember that the goals do not have to be specific, even if you have a general or vague goal then indicate that you DO have a goal for that category.     For example, one person may have a goal to cook their own dinner every night while you might not care at all whether you cook or eat out or order take out.   Also, goals can be either a desire to DO something as well as a desire to NOT DO something. - Diet

Remember that the goals do not have to be specific, even if you have a general or vague goal then indicate that you DO have a goal for that category.     For example, one person may have a goal to cook their own dinner every night while you might not care at all whether you cook or eat out or order take out.   Also, goals can be either a desire to DO something as well as a desire to NOT DO something. - Administrative work (taxes, banking, etc.)

value_overall_1: Attributes | Overall    Think about the attributes you provided or chose above, as well as any others that are important to you that you did not include.    To what degree do you believe you are actually fulfilling or achieving all of the attributes you value? - Achieving all valued attributes (%)
overall_success_post_1: Intention/Goal Success    We would like to ask you once again:     Overall, When you consider all of the intentions and goals that you have for yourself, to whatdegree do you feel like you are successful in actually accomplishing these goals and intentions?    - 100% success rate would mean that you are able to accomplish ALL of your goals/intentions.  - 50% success rate would mean that you are able to accomplish about HALF of your goals/intentions. - Goal success rate (%)
meta_potential_4: Ability | Potential    What percentage of your POTENTIAL ABILITY do you feel like you are currently fulfilling?     In other words, how close do you think the actual version of yourself is to the best possible version? - Potential Realized (%)
meta_gap_cause_1: Gap Cause     Please indicate what proportion of this gap is due to you (internal) and what proportion of the gap is due to outside forces (external)?    In terms of outside forces this could be things like systemic racism, economic limitations, your sex/gender, a global pandemic, or just bad luck. - The cause of my gap is:
meta_own_expect_4: Expectations | Own    What percentage of your OWN EXPECTATIONS do you feel like you are currently fulfilling?   In other words, how close do you think the actual version of yourself is to the version you EXPECT yourself to be? - Own Expectations Realized (%)
meta_other_expect_4: Expectations | Others    What percentage of OTHERS EXPECTATIONS (society, friends, family) do you feel like you are currently fulfilling? debrief_form_1: University of Toronto, Scarborough  Debriefing Form   Principle Investigator: Cendri Hutcherson, Ph.D., Assistant Professor of PsychologProject Name: Tracking the gap between goals and outcomes in daily behavior Thank you for participating in our study!  We designed this study to better understand how people might experience a gap between their intentions and behavior, both at a day to day level, and at a broader life level. We hope to develop a better measurement of this gap that is reliable across contexts and across individuals.  Please understand that your participation in the research is voluntary and that you are free to withdraw your consent and data in the research at this time without any penalties. That is, you will receive full credit and payment for taking part in the study. Should you choose to withdraw from the study, all of the information that we obtained from your session will be destroyed. Thank you for your time and effort in our study.
